import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.boxplot(data['distance'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts()
    top_20_origin_counts = origin_counts[:20]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.bar(top_20_origin_counts.index, top_20_origin_counts.values)
    ax.set_title('What is the most common origin airport?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin Airport')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(ticker.FuncFormatter(lambda x, _: pd.to_datetime(x).strftime('%Y-%m-%d')))
    plt.plot(data.groupby('date').size())
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights across different dates?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
